pageContext.description: Dimensions: L 127.7 mm; We 44mm; Wbt 20.8mm; B st. 31.1mm; Blp (curve) 8.5mm; T sep 14.2 mm; Tbt 5mm,Typology: rounded st. and fg. crests; some flattening at fg. ends; rect. septum end; lp. placed off centre; tendancy to facets at very top of blade angles, under stop,Manufacture: cg. fls. almost fully removed - merest bumb on lp. and reverse side; good blade tip hollows; curved irregular bevel created high on blade with hammer works below; slight tendency for close edge bevel on one face; moulding dimples in septums, flange sides, mdev stop etc.,Condition: butt end broken surface; edge mainly intact and sharp; small chip to one side - purply brown, probably just corrosion damage; fg. and stops virtually undamaged.,Attached Material: yellowy fawn soil tracel
